A fitness function is usually set to be a distance or a loss function, as the optimization process evolves to minimize a score. In this work, the fitness function is defined as the sum of square error (SSE):3SSE=∑j=080(αλj−αtarget,λj)2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
