It is important to understand that the magnitude of the average absorption coefficient is scalable according to the particle concentration [see Eq. (2)]. Therefore, if the target absorption coefficient spectrum is satisfied, controlling its magnitude to a certain value can be easily done by simply changing the volume fraction of nanoparticles. In the forthcoming analysis, the average of the absorption coefficient was set to 1 cm−1 for simplicity. Here, α=1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
